{"id":14880788,"mediaExerciseId":"dbd0833d-7925-489f-b91b-23f61397e8e7","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612274,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":84,"solutions":[{"id":5908584,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are will learn about common-size financial statements and common-base year statements.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/60ee45792c0617068ade800f8e460efd/13064541955c9b727dc9b0a6f7c8e57d/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/60ee45792c0617068ade800f8e460efd/13064541955c9b727dc9b0a6f7c8e57d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define financial statements.\n\n**Financial statements** are formal records which shows the financial activities and performance of a company.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/60ee45792c0617068ade800f8e460efd/a7fddcac0eb2967b577b4f7189dac0d6/lateximg_large.png","width":1030},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/60ee45792c0617068ade800f8e460efd/a7fddcac0eb2967b577b4f7189dac0d6/lateximg.png","width":516}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**Common-size statements** or also known as vertical analysis, expresses all balance sheet accounts as a percentage of total assets and all income statement accounts as a percentage of total sales. It is best used in comparing business of different size or type.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/60ee45792c0617068ade800f8e460efd/07e03a4a2f46e2e9e0a90ff537f46edd/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/60ee45792c0617068ade800f8e460efd/07e03a4a2f46e2e9e0a90ff537f46edd/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"\n**Common-base year statements** shows the growth rate in an account by choosing a base year and express each line item respective to the base amount.  It is useful when comparing current data with the base year.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/60ee45792c0617068ade800f8e460efd/3d1613b5ddc99493d0710b0f601e7723/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/60ee45792c0617068ade800f8e460efd/3d1613b5ddc99493d0710b0f601e7723/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"91371706-2106-49c2-9f2e-b193aa46fc85","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880789,"exerciseName":"6","page":84,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"cd042b18-5dbc-4d